#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn12.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Dasabalavagga "
msgstr "3. The Ten Powers "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Aññatitthiyasutta "
msgstr "24. Followers of Other Paths "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn12.24:1.1"
msgid "Rājagahe viharati veḷuvane. "
msgstr "Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Sāriputta robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Rājagaha for alms. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to him, "

msgctxt "sn12.24:1.4"
msgid "“atippago kho tāva rājagahe piṇḍāya carituṃ. "
msgstr "“It’s too early to wander for alms in Rājagaha. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:1.5"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.33, sc2
msgctxt "sn12.24:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then he went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths, and exchanged greetings with the wanderers there. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:2.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. The wanderers said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn12.24:3.1"
msgid "“Santāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṃkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti. "
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, there are ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. Some of them declare that suffering is made by oneself. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.2"
msgid "Santi panāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā paraṃkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti. "
msgstr "Some of them declare that suffering is made by another. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.3"
msgid "Santāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṃkatañca paraṃkatañca dukkhaṃ paññapenti. "
msgstr "Some of them declare that suffering is made by both oneself and another. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.4"
msgid "Santi panāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṃkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti. "
msgstr "Some of them declare that suffering arises by chance, not made by oneself or another. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.5"
msgid "Idha, panāvuso sāriputta, samaṇo gotamo kiṃvādī kimakkhāyī? "
msgstr "What does the ascetic Gotama say about this? How does he explain it? "

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.6"
msgid "Kathaṃ byākaramānā ca mayaṃ vuttavādino ceva samaṇassa gotamassa assāma, na ca samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyāma, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyyāma, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyyā”ti? "
msgstr "How should we answer so as to repeat what the ascetic Gotama has said, and not misrepresent him with an untruth? How should we explain in line with his teaching, with no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn12.24:4.1"
msgid "“Paṭiccasamuppannaṃ kho, āvuso, dukkhaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā. "
msgstr "“Reverends, the Buddha said that suffering is dependently originated. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:4.2"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca? "
msgstr "Dependent on what? "

msgctxt "sn12.24:4.3"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca. "
msgstr "Dependent on contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:4.4"
msgid "Iti vadaṃ vuttavādī ceva bhagavato assa, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyya. "
msgstr "If you said this you would repeat what the Buddha has said, and not misrepresent him with an untruth. You would explain in line with his teaching, and there would be no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.34, sc5
msgctxt "sn12.24:5.1"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself, that’s conditioned by contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:5.2"
msgid "Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā paraṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by another, that’s also conditioned by contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:5.3"
msgid "Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself and another, that’s also conditioned by contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:5.4"
msgid "Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "In the case of those who declare that suffering arises by chance, not made by oneself or another, that’s also conditioned by contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn12.24:6.1"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself, it’s impossible that they will experience that without contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:6.2"
msgid "Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā paraṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by another, it’s impossible that they will experience that without contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:6.3"
msgid "Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself and another, it’s impossible that they will experience that without contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:6.4"
msgid "Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti. "
msgstr "In the case of those who declare that suffering arises by chance, not made by oneself or another, it’s impossible that they will experience that without contact.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn12.24:7.1"
msgid "Assosi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato sāriputtassa tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ. "
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda heard this discussion between Venerable Sāriputta and those wanderers who follow other paths. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:7.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando rājagahe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then Ānanda wandered for alms in Rājagaha. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "sn12.24:7.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako āyasmato sāriputtassa tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ ahosi kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi. "
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn12.24:8.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, ānanda, yathā taṃ sāriputto sammā byākaramāno byākareyya. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Ānanda! It’s just as Sāriputta has so rightly explained. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:8.2"
msgid "Paṭiccasamuppannaṃ kho, ānanda, dukkhaṃ vuttaṃ mayā. "
msgstr "I have said that suffering is dependently originated. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:8.3"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca? "
msgstr "Dependent on what? "

msgctxt "sn12.24:8.4"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca. "
msgstr "Dependent on contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.24:8.5"
msgid "Iti vadaṃ vuttavādī ceva me assa, na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyya. "
msgstr "Saying this you would repeat what I have said, and not misrepresent me with an untruth. You would explain in line with my teaching, and there would be no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.35, sc9
msgctxt "sn12.24:9.1"
msgid "Tatrānanda, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself, that’s conditioned by contact. … "

msgctxt "sn12.24:9.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe … "
msgstr " "

